# Format borrowed from Crafty's start.pgn. "!" indicated a move that 
# should be played.  
#
# The openings included here are from Marc Lacrosse's Most Frequent Lines test: MLmfl test
#
# http://sites.google.com/site/chessbazaar/2007-01-2008-fast-engine-testing-the-mlmfl-test
#
# The idea behind using these lines is that these are the positions
# used in testing improvements in EXchess, so these lines should be
# reasonable choices as starting moves.   Right now, they all are
# being used for both sides, but I will eventually do some analysis
# on EXchess' results on these positions and cull them a bit.
#
#
# Last modified: 2010_08_22
#

[ MLmfl-01 ]
1.e4! c5! 2.Nf3! d6! 3.d4! cxd4! 4.Nxd4! Nf6! 5.Nc3! a6! 6.Be3! e6! 7.f3!

